original: Jarnås, Karl Samuel, läroverksadjunkt, Skara, f. 17/11/89 i Kyrkas, Ska-rab. 1. G. 20 m. Vendela Sofia Nor-lander. Barn: Lars f. 21, Ingrid 25, Anna-Karin 31. — Stud:ex. i Skara 09, fil. mag. i Gbg 14, provår v. Gbgs h. latin 19. Res. t. Norge 18, Tyskl. o. Danm. 21, Danm. o. Engl. 26, Tyskl. o. Tjeckoslov. 28. Vik. adj. i Borås 15, ämneslär. v. Sävsjö prakt. sk. 16, vik. dito i Falkenberg 16, vik. adj. i Norrtälje 17, i Söderhamn s. å., e. o. adj. v. Luleå folksk:sem. 17-18, vik. ämneslär. v. Ludvika komm. mellan-sk. 18-19, vik. adj. v. Gbgs ö. realsk. 19, vik. lektor v. Gbgs. latin 19-20, vik. adj. i Vänersborg 20-23, adj. i Strängnäs 23, adj. i tyska o. eng. v. Skara h. a. 1. sed. 29.
translated: Jarnås, Karl Samuel, upper secondary school teacher, Skara, born on November 17, 1889 in Kyrkas, Skaraborg County. Married on June 20, 19xx to Vendela Sofia Norlander. Children: Lars, born in 1921, Ingrid in 1925, Anna-Karin in 1931. - Graduated from Skara Latin School in 1909, obtained a Master of Arts degree in Gothenburg in 1914, completed a probationary year at Gothenburg Higher Latin School in 1919. Traveled to Norway in 1918, Germany and Denmark in 1921, Denmark and England in 1926, Germany and Czechoslovakia in 1928. Worked temporarily as an assistant in Borås in 1915, as a subject teacher at Sävsjö Practical School in 1916, as a temporary assistant in Falkenberg in 1916, as a temporary assistant in Norrtälje in 1917, in Söderhamn the same year, as a substitute assistant at Luleå Elementary School Seminarie from 1917 to 1918, as a temporary subject teacher at Ludvika Municipal Middle School from 1918 to 1919, as a temporary assistant at Gothenburg East Real School in 1919, as a substitute lecturer at Gothenburg Latin School from 1919 to 1920, as a temporary assistant in Vänersborg from 1920 to 1923, as an assistant in Strängnäs in 1923, as an assistant in German and English at Skara Higher School since 1929.
